    "The source XML was created by OCR, without correction or content editing, and encoded at TEI in Libraries Level 1.",
    "A and x are alternative streams and must never be summed as two works.",
    "The XML x label is an 1886 editorial-stream label, not the later 1894 stemmatic branch v and not a witness siglum.",
    "A metrics exclude all NOTE1 descendants; x metrics additionally exclude the nonverse display L '2071 ff.:'.",
    "Carl Schmirgel's appendix is omitted and therefore does not create a work-level metadata responsibility.",
    "Only the parent content part has item_count=1; all representation children have item_count=null.",
    "Part II's title is imprinted 1886 while its preliminary forewords are dated October 1887; the chronology remains explicit rather than normalized away.",
    "D-MER's work-level form account places chiefly six-line tail-rhyme stanzas in lines 1-474 and rhyming couplets from line 475 to the end; retain that transition as qualified form description only, without adding representation line totals. The metadata lineage-binding schema uses coarse roles: source_package and page_image_carrier map to related_source; transcription_base, missing_leaf_supply, collated_witness, selected_variant_source, transcription_base_and_collated_source, collated_fragment, and supporting_witness map to source_witness; parallel_scholarly_edition and abstract_source_work map to related_source. Exact functions remain explicit in the lineage relations and their scopes."
